From f2c3460fb100b88018f246a85a9389265b5957e9 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ramesh Mandal <ramesh@6epixels.com>
Date: Thu, 2 Jul 2026 19:00:21 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] feat(consent): approval-gated messaging - request, accept,
 deny, block, report

Server (all enforced server-side, 13/13 tests):
- connection registry: request -> pending -> accepted; mutual requests
  auto-accept; deny clears and allows re-requesting
- dm/typing gated on ACCEPTED connection (in addition to public
  visibility); private overrides even accepted connections
- block: mutual severance, invisible to the blocked party (their
  requests are swallowed but acknowledged as normal pending); unblock
  does NOT restore the connection - consent must be re-earned
- report: minimal privacy-conscious log (no content exists to log),
  auto-blocks
- two-tier leak resistance: strangers get uniform not_connected;
  connected-but-private and connected-but-offline are indistinguishable
- connections snapshot sent on hello

Extension:
- ConsentPanel replaces the composer for every non-accepted state:
  send request / waiting / accept-deny-block-report with explicit
  privacy consent copy / declined + re-request / blocked + unblock
- incoming requests appear as unread inbox conversations with a
  system notice; accept/decline/block outcomes land as system notices
- Communities rows show live status chips (Connect / Requested /
  Respond / Blocked / message icon)
- typing relayed only on accepted connections
- dm_error not_connected handled
